'''Kamiichinomiya Ōawa Shrine''' (上一宮大粟神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Kamiyama, Tokushima|ja|神山町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Myōzai District|ja|名西郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is one of the disputed shrines ({{ill|Ronsha|ja|論社|1=candidate shrines|2=ja|3=論社|lt=candidate|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) claiming to be the {{ill|Ichinomiya|ja|一宮|1=Ichinomiya|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of {{ill|Awa Province|ja|阿波国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, identified with the "Ama no Iwatowake Yakurahime Shrine" (天石門別八倉比売神社) mentioned in the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>Other claimants include {{ill|Yakurahime Shrine|ja|八倉比売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Ichinomiya Shrine (Tokushima)|ja|一宮神社 (徳島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.</ref> Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and it is No. 73 on the {{ill|New Shikoku Mandala Pilgrimage|ja|新四国曼荼羅霊場|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Enshrined deity ==
* {{ill|Ōgetsuhime|ja|オオゲツヒメ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Ōgetsuhime no Mikoto) — also known as Amanoiwatowake Yakurahime no Mikoto (天石門別八倉比売命) or Ōawa-hime no Mikoto (大粟比売命).

According to shrine tradition, Ōgetsuhime traveled from the Niwa region of {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (present-day {{ill|Taki, Mie|ja|多気町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) to Awa Province on horseback and introduced the cultivation of {{ill|millet|ja|粟|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the area.

