In {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3 (1870 CE), the shrine was renamed "Haniuneya Shrine" (埴生女屋神社), but due to petitions from the local parishioners, it was restored to its current name, Kamiichinomiya Ōawa Shrine, in Meiji 28 (1895 CE).

